eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila visited the Ndzondos and filed this report. #DStv403 EAST LONDON - Almost two years after losing four relatives to Covid-19, the Ndzondo family says the scars are still deep. What hit the family hardest was not being able to give their relatives a dignified send-off in the traditional sense, because of Covid-19 restrictions. As we reflect on the pandemic, eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila visited the Ndzondo's.